org.cef.handler

Class CefResourceHandlerAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cef.handler.CefResourceHandlerAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CefResourceHandler 

    public abstract class CefResourceHandlerAdapter
extends java.lang.Object
implements CefResourceHandler
    An abstract adapter class for receiving resource requests. The methods in this class are empty. This class exists as convenience for creating handler objects.(用于接收资源请求的抽象适配器类。此类中的方法为空。此类的存在是为了方便创建处理程序对象。)

      • getResponseHeaders

        public void getResponseHeaders(CefResponse response,
                               IntRef responseLength,
                               StringRef redirectUrl)
        Description copied from interface: CefResourceHandler
        Retrieve response header information. If the response length is not known set |responseLength| to -1 and readResponse() will be called until it returns false. If the response length is known set |responseLength| to a positive value and readResponse() will be called until it returns false or the specified number of bytes have been read. Use the |response| object to set the mime type, http status code and other optional header values.(检索响应标头信息。如果响应长度未知，则将|responseLength|设置为-1，并将调用readResponse()，直到返回false。如果响应长度已知，请将|responseLength|设置为正值，并将调用readResponse()，直到它返回false或读取指定的字节数。使用|response|对象设置mime类型、http状态代码和其他可选的响应头值。)
        Specified by:
        getResponseHeaders in interface CefResourceHandler
        Parameters:
        response - The request response that should be returned. Instance only valid within the scope of this method.(response-应返回的请求响应。实例仅在此方法的范围内有效。)
        responseLength - Optionally set the response length if known.(responseLength-如果已知，可选择设置响应长度。)
        redirectUrl - Optionally redirect the request to a new URL.(redirectUrl-可选择将请求重定向到新的URL。)

      • open

        public boolean open(CefRequest request,
                    BoolRef handleRequest,
                    CefCallback callback)
        Description copied from interface: CefResourceHandler
        Open the response stream. This and related (getResponseHeaders, read, skip) methods will be called in sequence but not from a dedicated thread.

        For backwards compatibility set |handleRequest| to false and return false and the processRequest() method will be called.

        (打开响应流。此方法和相关（getResponseHeaders、read、skip）方法将按顺序调用，但不会从专用线程调用。 为了向后兼容，将|handleRequest|设置为false并返回false，然后将调用 processRequest() 方法。)
        Specified by:
        open in interface CefResourceHandler
        Parameters:
        request - The request itself. Cannot be modified in this callback. Instance only valid within the scope of this method.(request-请求本身。无法在此回调中修改。实例仅在此方法的范围内有效。)
        handleRequest - Set to true to handle/cancel the request immediately(handleRequest -设置为true以立即 处理/取消 请求 )
        callback - Callback to continue or cancel the request at a later time(callback - 回调以继续或稍后取消请求)
        Returns:
        True to handle the request(处理请求返回true)

      • read

        public boolean read(byte[] dataOut,
                    int bytesToRead,
                    IntRef bytesRead,
                    CefResourceReadCallback callback)
        Description copied from interface: CefResourceHandler
        Read response data. If data is available immediately copy up to |bytesToRead| bytes into |dataOut|, set |bytesRead| to the number of bytes copied, and return true. To read the data at a later time store |dataOut|, set |bytesRead| to 0, return true and call the callback when the data is available. To indicate response completion set |bytesRead| to 0 and return false. To indicate failure set |bytesRead| to <0 (e.g. -2 for ERR_FAILED) and return false.

        For backwards compatibility set |bytesRead| to -1 and return false and the readResponse() method will be called.

        (读取响应数据。如果数据可用，请立即将最多|bytesToRead|个字节复制到|dataOut|中，将|bytesRead|设置为复制的字节数，并返回true。若要在以后读取数据，请存储|dataOut|，将|bytesRead|设置为0，返回true，并在数据可用时调用回调。若要指示响应完成，请将|bytesRead|设置为0并返回false。要表示失败，请将|bytesRead|设置为<0（例如，ERR_FAILED为-2）并返回false。
        为了向后兼容，将|bytesRead|设置为-1并返回false，将调用 readResponse() 方法。)
        Specified by:
        read in interface CefResourceHandler
        Parameters:
        dataOut - Write data to this buffer. Buffer remains valid until either an immediate response is delivered (return true) or the callback is called later when data is available (return false).(dataOut -将数据写入此缓冲区。缓冲区保持有效，直到立即传递响应（返回true）或稍后在数据可用时调用回调（返回true）。)
        bytesToRead - Size of the buffer.(bytesToRead-缓冲区的大小。)
        bytesRead - Number of bytes written to the buffer.(bytesRead-写入缓冲区的字节数。)
        callback - Callback to execute if data will be available asynchronously.(callback-如果数据将以异步方式可用，则执行回调。)
        Returns:
        True if more data is or will be available.(如果有或将有更多数据可用，则为True。)

        public boolean readResponse(byte[] dataOut,
                            int bytesToRead,
                            IntRef bytesRead,
                            CefCallback callback)
        Description copied from interface: CefResourceHandler
        Read response data. If data is available immediately copy up to |bytesToRead| bytes into |dataOut|, set |bytesRead| to the number of bytes copied, and return true. To read the data at a later time set |bytesRead| to 0, return true and call CefCallback.Continue() when the data is available. To indicate response completion return false.(读取响应数据。如果数据可用，请立即将最多|bytesToRead|个字节复制到|dataOut|中，将|bytesRead|设置为复制的字节数，然后返回true。若要稍后读取数据，请将|bytesRead|设置为0，返回true并在数据可用时调用CefCallback.Continute()。返回false表示响应完成。)
        Specified by:
        readResponse in interface CefResourceHandler
        Parameters:
        dataOut - Write data to this buffer.(dataOut-将数据写入该缓冲区。)
        bytesToRead - Size of the buffer.(bytesToRead-缓冲区的大小。)
        bytesRead - Number of bytes written to the buffer.(bytesRead-写入缓冲区的字节数。)
        callback - Callback to execute if data will be available asynchronously.(callback-如果数据将以异步方式可用，则执行回调。)
        Returns:
        True if more data is or will be available.(如果有或将有更多数据可用，则为True。)

      • skip

        public boolean skip(long bytesToSkip,
                    LongRef bytesSkipped,
                    CefResourceSkipCallback callback)
        Description copied from interface: CefResourceHandler
        Skip response data when requested by a Range header. Skip over and discard |bytesToSkip| bytes of response data. If data is available immediately set |bytesSkipped| to the number of bytes skipped and return true. To read the data at a later time set |bytesSkipped| to 0, return true and execute |callback| when the data is available. To indicate failure set |bytesSkipped| to < 0 (e.g. -2 for ERR_FAILED) and return false.(当Range标头请求时跳过响应数据。跳过并丢弃|bytesToSkip|字节的响应数据。如果数据立即可用，则将|bytesSkipped|设置为跳过的字节数，并返回true。若要在稍后在|bytesSkipped|设置为0时读取数据，请返回true，并在数据可用时执行|callback|。要表示失败，请将|bytesSkipped|设置为<0（例如，ERR_FAILED为-2）并返回false。)
        Specified by:
        skip in interface CefResourceHandler
        Parameters:
        bytesToSkip - Number of bytes to skip.(bytesToSkip -要跳过的字节数。)
        bytesSkipped - Number of bytes skipped.(bytesSkipped -跳过的字节数。)
        callback - Callback to execute if data will be skipped asynchronously.(callback-如果数据将被异步跳过，则执行回调。)
